title: Umm Salal | QSL
snippet: Umm Salal Sports Club was founded in 1979 under the name of Al Tadamun Sports Club. The name was changed to Umm Salal in 2004 due to the club’s location. Nicknamed the Barzan’s Falcons and The Orange Fortress, Umm Salal made their debut in the Qatar League in the 2006-07 season.

title: Umm Salal SC - Club profile | Transfermarkt
snippet: In 2004, it was renamed Umm Salal Sports Club, reflecting its location in Doha’s Umm Salal district. The first football team, nicknamed the “Barzan Falcons” and “The Orange Fortress,” achieved promotion to the Qatar Stars League in the 2006–2007 season.
